Pfizer Plans to Cut Spanish Workforce by 11%, Expansion Reports

-- B y   M a n u e l   B a i g o r r i
-- 
2011-09-21T06:49:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-21/pfizer-plans-to-cut-spanish-workforce-by-11-expansion-reports.html
Pfizer Inc (PFE)  plans to cut its
workforce in  Spain  by 11 percent, or 220 employees, because of
the financial crisis in  Europe  and Spanish regulatory measures
to reduce pharmaceutical spending,  Expansion  reported.  The cuts will affect the administrative and sales forces,
while employees at Pfizer’s plants in Madrid and Olot in Girona
province won’t be affected, the newspaper said, citing the
company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Manuel Baigorri in Madrid at 
 mbaigorri@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Angela Cullen at 
 acullen8@bloomberg.net  